
In CICD we are using docker registry url , username and password that was managed by System management(parameter store)

In terraform we are dealing with access key and secrete key also managedy by system management(parameter store).

In application we are using Data base passwords are externalized by the secrets , that managed by the secret management. why beacause it's high 
sensitive data. 

Here secrete management is costing more than system management that is the reason where ever it applicable we are using secrete management. 
If some data i,e not much sensitive we are using system management(parameter store)as parameter only to reduce the cost. 

In secrete management there is a mechanism that for the certificate , even public key was exposed that can be rotate foe every 90/180 days. 
Also for Database password are can be rotate once in a 2/3 days. This way secrete management will provide more secure. 

In some cases for the microservices API tokens also more sensitive ,in such a case we are implementing security management. 

TO retrive the data from the AWS platform , we need to create IAM role and assign it to system & secrete management. 

Configuring system management is very simple and it's very fast retrive the data. 


